07/12/2006
ROME, Italy -- During a meeting with Macedonian counterpart Nikola Gruevski in Rome on Wednesday (December 6th), Prime Minister Romano Prodi reaffirmed his country's support for Macedonia's EU aspirations. Prodi said he recently sent a letter to the leaders of the EU member states, calling on them to provide concrete incentives for Macedonia and Croatia. Prodi and Gruevski also discussed how Italy could help Macedonia combat organised crime and corruption. (Vecer - 07/12/06; Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 06/12/06)
